relays,” Lewis said. “We need to
be prepared for the upcoming
weeks.”

The highest finisher for Pitt
was the 4 x 400 relay team
(Katina Miles, Ronise Crumpler,
Monica Hockaday, Kim Blair)
with a third—place finish.

Crumpler, Blair and Hockaday
joined Tonia Malloy in the sprint
medley relay to take fourth
place, barely missing a Pitt
record with a time of 3:54.25
minutes.

“This is the first time they’ve
run the sprint medley,” Lewis
said. “They ran a great race.”

Crumpler also competed indi-

vidually, taking seventh place in.

the 400-meter event.
